  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/PegasysEng/artemis/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/PegasysEng/artemis/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3APegasysEng/Artemis -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nBls spec tests does not include inputs for `verify` methods but in block processing operations spec tests there is a lot of bls signatures to be verified. It seems that your `bls.verify` does not work. That said, it seems that with same private key it produces different signature than py_ecc which lead me to believe that hash_to_g2 implementation doesn't work always.\r\nWe used similar implementation in Lodestar which also seems to have similar issue.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\nInputs from `test_process_deposit.test_new_deposit` spec tests which passes in py_ecc. Do note, domain in hex is `0000000003000000` (not really sure why do you use long).\r\n```java\r\n  @Test\r\n  void succeedsWhenAMessageSignsAndVerifies() throws BLSException {\r\n    assertTrue(\r\n      BLSSignature\r\n              .fromBytes(\r\n                      Bytes.fromHexString(\r\n                              \"a61b0de0d96c0f7a99874ba327e0ed4715e2bbe125ee0148e43179ea508c84e3c7aaf0a3248e414d13f28e7c9eed568a15f58373f8d49c595008d67ebfa5b5536b46b05f840f83931fd5730c88e4c4876175623453d2087d616302941010534f\"\r\n                      )\r\n              ).checkSignature(\r\n              BLSPublicKey.fromBytesCompressed(Bytes.fromHexString(\"b4ea54b24c3dae4c5d072e75299096f9c3d4c6902112bdb45ef18281bfc4143b240662d454316092acebafdc7fb427cb\")),\r\n              Bytes.fromHexString(\"2ae827264d2182d3a9c4d5c2e8b09b85ca9daf499771cf4200bd67cd3bfcdf25\"),\r\n              12884901888L\r\n      )\r\n\r\n    );\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\ntrue\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nfalse\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\n100%\r\n\r\n",
